  description="Joint IBM, Cisco, and Fermilab SQMS plan to build a networked distributed quantum-computing system by the early 2030s, with a proof-of-concept demonstration targeted for end-of-2030. Announced 20 November 2025. Three components — microwave-to-optical transducers, Quantum Networking Units at each node, and inter-cryostat entanglement-distribution protocols — are named as not yet shipping at scale."
